================================================================================
Third-Party Licenses
================================================================================

The following third-party projects are referenced, reimplemented, or used by
gswarp. Users must comply with the respective license terms.


--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. 3D Gaussian Splatting for Real-Time Radiance Field Rendering
   https://repo-sam.inria.fr/fungraph/3d-gaussian-splatting/
   License: Gaussian-Splatting License (non-commercial research only)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

gswarp is a clean-room reimplementation of the differentiable Gaussian
rasterization pipeline originally developed as part of the 3D Gaussian Splatting
project. The algorithm design and pipeline structure follow the original CUDA
implementation. Usage of gswarp is therefore subject to the upstream license
terms reproduced below.

  Inria and the Max Planck Institut for Informatik (MPII) hold all the ownership
  rights on the Software named "3D Gaussian Splatting for Real-Time Radiance
  Field Rendering".

  The Software is provided for research purposes only. Any other use, in
  particular any use for commercial purposes, is prohibited. This includes,
  without limitation, incorporation in a commercial product, use in a commercial
  service, or production of other artefacts for commercial purposes.

  Authors:
    Bernhard Kerbl (bernhard.kerbl@tugraz.at)
    Georgios Kopanas (gkopanas@gmail.com)
    Thomas Leimkühler (thomas.leimkuehler@mpi-inf.mpg.de)
    George Drettakis (george.drettakis@inria.fr)


--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. NVIDIA Warp
   https://nvidia.github.io/warp/
   License: Apache License 2.0
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

gswarp uses NVIDIA Warp as its GPU kernel runtime. Warp is distributed under the
Apache License 2.0. A copy of the license is available at:
https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0


--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3. PyTorch
   https://pytorch.org/
   License: BSD-style (PyTorch License)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

gswarp uses PyTorch for tensor management, autograd integration, and CUDA memory
allocation. PyTorch is distributed under a BSD-style license. A copy of the
license is available at:
https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/blob/main/LICENSE


--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4. Fast Converging 3D Gaussian Splatting for 1-Minute Reconstruction
   https://arxiv.org/abs/2601.19489
   Authors: Ziyu Zhang, Tianle Liu, Diantao Tu, Shuhan Shen
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The tight AABB bounding-box technique used in gswarp is inspired by this work.
Only the algorithmic idea is adopted; no source code from this project is
included. The paper is available under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0.
